260
00:08:40,423 --> 00:08:42,703
- What was that? That startled me. - Something opened up.

261
00:08:44,793 --> 00:08:45,933
(A secret door opens.)

262
00:08:46,133 --> 00:08:47,833
- It's open. - What's this?

263
00:08:47,963 --> 00:08:49,703
- What is it? - Is that an exit?

264
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:51,833
Open it.

265
00:08:52,303 --> 00:08:53,872
- What's going on? - This has been here the whole time?

266
00:08:53,873 --> 00:08:54,902
- Let's go in. - What is this?

267
00:08:54,903 --> 00:08:56,142
- What is this place? - It's...

268
00:08:56,143 --> 00:08:57,143
What?

269
00:08:57,343 --> 00:08:59,343
- What is it? - It says, "From Wannable."

270
00:09:00,413 --> 00:09:03,082
(They open up the door that's been hidden this whole time.)

271
00:09:03,083 --> 00:09:04,083
- What is it? - What?

272
00:09:05,613 --> 00:09:06,783
I can't go in there.

273
00:09:06,983 --> 00:09:08,522
- Why not? - Let's go inside.

274
00:09:08,523 --> 00:09:10,252
- This feels a bit weird. - What?

275
00:09:10,253 --> 00:09:11,253
What is it?

276
00:09:11,293 --> 00:09:13,999
(With Ji Hoon leading the way in, they finally enter the secret room.)

277
00:09:14,023 --> 00:09:16,623
(This secret room at the Wanna Base is...)

278
00:09:17,093 --> 00:09:18,863
(The light sticks that symbolize Wannables)

279
00:09:19,263 --> 00:09:24,973
(Memorabilia filled with the history of Wanna One)

280
00:09:26,203 --> 00:09:31,573
(Thousands of fans have been cherishing their journey.)

281
00:09:32,613 --> 00:09:35,413
(The 12th room at the Wanna Base has always been there for them.)

282
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:38,053
(Room of Wannable)

283
00:09:38,353 --> 00:09:39,353
My gosh.

284
00:09:40,883 --> 00:09:41,883
What is this?

285
00:09:42,283 --> 00:09:43,283
Oh, my.

286
00:09:45,023 --> 00:09:47,422
Our fans wrote letters to us.

287
00:09:47,423 --> 00:09:49,422
(Pictures of Wannables and their handwritten letters...)

288
00:09:49,423 --> 00:09:50,462
(fill the wall.)

289
00:09:50,463 --> 00:09:51,762
(We're meeting again as spring comes to an end.)

290
00:09:51,763 --> 00:09:52,992
(It's been 7 years since we met. But you guys hadn't changed.)

291
00:09:52,993 --> 00:09:54,779
(I'm so happy that I got to meet you guys as a Wannable again.)

292
00:09:54,803 --> 00:10:00,233
(Wanna One can't look away from the years of their love.)

293
00:10:01,303 --> 00:10:05,312
(The letters are filled with words left unsaid for 7 years.)

294
00:10:05,313 --> 00:10:09,313
(The letters are filled with words left unsaid for 7 years.)

295
00:10:09,813 --> 00:10:11,313
When did they write all this?

296
00:10:14,783 --> 00:10:17,723
(During the opening ceremony, April 6, 2026)

297
00:10:18,193 --> 00:10:20,553
(After Wanna One left after the reunion of 7 years, )

298
00:10:22,123 --> 00:10:27,163
(countless Wannables stayed behind to share their untold stories.)

299
00:10:32,603 --> 00:10:36,703
(They wrote a love letter, hoping it would reach Wanna One.)

300
00:10:36,903 --> 00:10:39,143
(I will remember you.)

301
00:10:41,083 --> 00:10:44,453
(Love piled up little by little and filled the Room of Wannable.)

302
00:10:47,253 --> 00:10:48,722
I guess they recently wrote the letters.

303
00:10:48,723 --> 00:10:49,752
(Wanna One reads the letters from Wannables.)

304
00:10:49,753 --> 00:10:51,833
They must have written the letters on the first day.

305
00:10:52,793 --> 00:10:55,822
All the letters inside are different.

306
00:10:55,823 --> 00:10:57,093
Yes. They're mixed up.

307
00:11:04,273 --> 00:11:05,433
It was so beautiful.

308
00:11:05,903 --> 00:11:07,543
It was really touching.

309
00:11:12,473 --> 00:11:14,343
Gosh, look at the ceiling.

310
00:11:14,513 --> 00:11:15,912
Look at the ceiling.

311
00:11:15,913 --> 00:11:17,182
(Everyone looks up at Ji Hoon's suggestion.)

312
00:11:17,183 --> 00:11:18,252
Look at that.

313
00:11:18,253 --> 00:11:19,452
(Everyone looks up at Ji Hoon's suggestion.)

314
00:11:19,453 --> 00:11:20,683
There's more on the ceiling?

315
00:11:22,753 --> 00:11:24,822
(The ceiling is decorated with the memories of Wannables.)

316
00:11:24,823 --> 00:11:26,523
There's more on the ceiling.

317
00:11:27,293 --> 00:11:30,993
(They've been rooting for Wanna One although things had changed.)

318
00:11:31,363 --> 00:11:32,363
Oh, my.

319
00:11:34,863 --> 00:11:38,202
I see photos of us at our concert in the Gocheok Sky Dome.

320
00:11:38,203 --> 00:11:40,243
(Wannables treasured the last moment of Wanna One.)

321
00:11:40,673 --> 00:11:42,303
"I'm so happy to see you guys again."

322
00:11:42,403 --> 00:11:44,443
"Thank you for keeping your promise."

323
00:11:46,613 --> 00:11:47,943
Honestly, I was quite scared.

324
00:11:49,413 --> 00:11:51,812
(My forever love, Wannables.)

325
00:11:51,813 --> 00:11:54,523
(I love you from the bottom of my heart.)

326
00:11:55,683 --> 00:11:58,722
We made numerous promises and comments.

327
00:11:58,723 --> 00:12:00,169
(Despite their promise to come back...)

328
00:12:00,193 --> 00:12:03,523
It took us 7 or 8 years to make good on our promise.

329
00:12:04,393 --> 00:12:07,092
But I saw that our fans...

330
00:12:07,093 --> 00:12:10,733
still loved and supported us as strongly as ever.

331
00:12:12,073 --> 00:12:14,172
This is so touching. Seriously.

332
00:12:14,173 --> 00:12:18,813
(Feeling grateful for their support, Wanna One reads the letters.)

333
00:12:19,273 --> 00:12:21,042
- Jae Hwan, there's one for you. - Thank you.

334
00:12:21,043 --> 00:12:22,812
She said you still looked good and didn't have to lose weight.

335
00:12:22,813 --> 00:12:23,983
Thank you.

336
00:12:25,953 --> 00:12:27,212
Did anyone write that for me?

337
00:12:27,213 --> 00:12:28,623
(Ruining the touching moment)

338
00:12:30,123 --> 00:12:32,152
- Did anyone write that for me? - They said you should lose weight.

339
00:12:32,153 --> 00:12:33,623
They said I should lose weight?

340
00:12:34,923 --> 00:12:36,622
Then should I lose more weight?

341
00:12:36,623 --> 00:12:37,632
Should I?

342
00:12:37,633 --> 00:12:39,962
(Wanna One jokes around and reads the letter...)

343
00:12:39,963 --> 00:12:42,323
(as they understand how deep their fans' love is for them.)

344
00:12:43,433 --> 00:12:44,433
(Startled)

345
00:12:44,733 --> 00:12:45,933
- What is it? - What?

346
00:12:46,603 --> 00:12:48,602
- I think there's a video message. - Where is it?

347
00:12:48,603 --> 00:12:50,002
I think there's a video message.

348
00:12:50,003 --> 00:12:51,212
- Where is it? - Where?

349
00:12:51,213 --> 00:12:53,212
I don't know. "I get shy on camera."

350
00:12:53,213 --> 00:12:54,782
"So I couldn't leave a video message."

351
00:12:54,783 --> 00:12:57,143
"But I'll do my best to express my support in this letter."

352
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:58,453
What?

353
00:12:59,583 --> 00:13:01,482
I see. She meant she'd do it in her private time.

354
00:13:01,483 --> 00:13:02,652
- So no video message. - I see.

355
00:13:02,653 --> 00:13:03,933
She'd do it in her private time?

356
00:13:04,923 --> 00:13:05,923
- She'd do it in her private time? - Oh, he got me.

357
00:13:05,924 --> 00:13:08,222
She said she might try leaving a video message.

358
00:13:08,223 --> 00:13:09,993
- Hello, Wanna One. - My goodness!

359
00:13:12,433 --> 00:13:14,333
- Hello, Wanna One. - My gosh.

360
00:13:14,933 --> 00:13:16,732
(The voices of Wannables call out to Wanna One.)

361
00:13:16,733 --> 00:13:18,472
- There is. - Yes, there is.

362
00:13:18,473 --> 00:13:19,473
There's one.

363
00:13:19,474 --> 00:13:21,979
(Wannables expressed their support through letters and video messages.)

364
00:13:22,003 --> 00:13:23,503
(Hello, Wanna One.)

365
00:13:28,183 --> 00:13:29,543
Wait, did they actually come here?

366
00:13:31,483 --> 00:13:32,652
- All I want to do. - All I want to do.

367
00:13:32,653 --> 00:13:35,222
- Hello, we're Wannables. - Hello, we're Wannables.

368
00:13:35,223 --> 00:13:36,223
I'm from Busan.

369
00:13:36,223 --> 00:13:37,223
I'm from Masan.

370
00:13:37,224 --> 00:13:38,392
I'm from Japan.

371
00:13:38,393 --> 00:13:40,123
I'm from China.

372
00:13:40,453 --> 00:13:43,392
I've been a fan since elementary school.

373
00:13:43,393 --> 00:13:44,792
Now, I'm in college.

374
00:13:44,793 --> 00:13:46,392
I came here to see Wanna One again.

375
00:13:46,393 --> 00:13:47,732
We're colleagues.

376
00:13:47,733 --> 00:13:49,602
We became close while talking about...

377
00:13:49,603 --> 00:13:50,832
- Wanna One. - That's how we became friends.

378
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:52,302
We both put on an act...

379
00:13:52,303 --> 00:13:53,632
and faked our illness to take a day off.

380
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:55,203
And we came here to see you.

381
00:13:56,243 --> 00:13:58,042
I didn't know this day would come.

382
00:13:58,043 --> 00:14:00,312
I missed Wanna One so much.

383
00:14:00,313 --> 00:14:01,342
I know it must have been tough,

384
00:14:01,343 --> 00:14:03,942
but thank you for making this reunion come true.

385
00:14:03,943 --> 00:14:06,682
It's been years since you last got together,

386
00:14:06,683 --> 00:14:08,853
so I hope you guys can have fun with good vibes.

387
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:10,623
I'm always rooting for you guys.

388
00:14:11,153 --> 00:14:12,423
I love you.

389
00:14:12,853 --> 00:14:14,192
Things have been tough...

390
00:14:14,193 --> 00:14:16,362
because I'm working part-time while I look for a permanent job.

391
00:14:16,363 --> 00:14:19,662
When I heard the news that you guys were coming back,

392
00:14:19,663 --> 00:14:20,663
I was over the moon.

393
00:14:20,664 --> 00:14:23,963
And I had been waiting for this day with so much excitement.

394
00:14:24,133 --> 00:14:28,372
Thank you for being part of my life.

395
00:14:28,373 --> 00:14:30,102
The biggest reason I studied Korean diligently...

396
00:14:30,103 --> 00:14:32,843
and decided to come to Korea for my studies...

397
00:14:33,243 --> 00:14:34,812
was Wanna One.

398
00:14:34,813 --> 00:14:37,283
Thank you for coming back to us.

399
00:14:38,583 --> 00:14:40,383
Thank you so much.

400
00:14:41,083 --> 00:14:43,683
Thank you for coming back, and I love you.

401
00:14:43,853 --> 00:14:44,993
Wanna One...

402
00:14:45,993 --> 00:14:47,992
is my youth.

403
00:14:47,993 --> 00:14:50,963
I'll always be waiting for you.

404
00:14:51,563 --> 00:14:54,563
I'll come and see you even after 10 or 20 years.

405
00:14:54,903 --> 00:14:58,402
I really hope that we get to see you again.

406
00:14:58,403 --> 00:15:00,332
I was in the ICU.

407
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:01,542
After getting discharged,

408
00:15:01,543 --> 00:15:04,843
I heard the news about your reunion.

409
00:15:05,213 --> 00:15:07,342
I was so grateful that I was still alive.

410
00:15:07,343 --> 00:15:09,512
I just want to say that's how long I had been waiting for you.

411
00:15:09,513 --> 00:15:11,512
Thank you so much.

412
00:15:11,513 --> 00:15:14,283
I'll live my life to the fullest while staying your fan.

413
00:15:14,653 --> 00:15:18,692
Thank you for being part of my youth.

414
00:15:18,693 --> 00:15:21,792
Thank you for saving my youth.

415
00:15:21,793 --> 00:15:23,492
I hope you continue to be part of my life.

416
00:15:23,493 --> 00:15:24,863
I love you, Wanna One.

417
00:15:25,293 --> 00:15:27,232
- Wanna One. Thank you... - Wanna One. Thank you...

418
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:28,702
- for keeping your promise that... - for keeping your promise that...

419
00:15:28,703 --> 00:15:30,132
- you'd come back after spring. - you'd come back after spring.

420
00:15:30,133 --> 00:15:31,279
- We love you. - We love you.

421
00:15:31,303 --> 00:15:33,503
I love you, Wanna One.

422
00:15:33,603 --> 00:15:36,442
I love you, Wanna One.

423
00:15:36,443 --> 00:15:39,273
- I love you, Wanna One. - I love you, Wanna One.

424
00:15:39,643 --> 00:15:41,012
I love you.

425
00:15:41,013 --> 00:15:42,183
We missed you.

426
00:15:43,883 --> 00:15:46,053
(I love you, Wanna One.)

427
00:15:55,593 --> 00:15:58,893
(They could feel Wannables' unwavering love from the video.)

428
00:16:00,563 --> 00:16:03,103
I could tell that they had been waiting for us all these years.

429
00:16:04,303 --> 00:16:06,173
I barely managed to hold back my tears.

430
00:16:07,173 --> 00:16:09,443
The group name, "Wanna One,"

431
00:16:09,943 --> 00:16:11,102
hits me pretty hard.

432
00:16:11,103 --> 00:16:12,373
I'm sure even our fans...

433
00:16:12,643 --> 00:16:15,383
couldn't be certain if they would get a chance...

434
00:16:15,913 --> 00:16:17,442
to see us together.

435
00:16:17,443 --> 00:16:19,683
(The name, "Wanna One," is enough to stir their hearts.)

436
00:16:19,913 --> 00:16:21,822
They must have been waiting for a long time.

437
00:16:21,823 --> 00:16:23,359
(Had it not been for their waiting, this couldn't have happened.)

438
00:16:23,383 --> 00:16:26,193
It made me wonder if we took too long, and I felt bad.

439
00:16:26,653 --> 00:16:28,463
Seeing how much they love us,

440
00:16:28,693 --> 00:16:32,163
I thought we should get together as Wanna One more often.

441
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:34,333
I kept getting goosebumps...

442
00:16:34,533 --> 00:16:37,602
because I had only dreamed of...

443
00:16:37,603 --> 00:16:40,103
hearing Wannables say things like...

444
00:16:40,573 --> 00:16:42,203
"We missed you," and "We love you."

445
00:16:42,373 --> 00:16:44,712
And seeing them say all these things in front of me...

446
00:16:44,713 --> 00:16:46,013
made me emotional.

447
00:16:46,513 --> 00:16:48,383
We made them wait for a long time.

448
00:16:48,813 --> 00:16:51,373
A big part of me wants to repay them for their love and support.

449
00:16:51,783 --> 00:16:52,952
We can start now.

450
00:16:52,953 --> 00:16:55,422
They gave us so much love for a year and a half.

451
00:16:55,423 --> 00:16:57,263
It's our turn to repay them for their support.

452
00:16:57,483 --> 00:16:58,952
We should work really hard.

453
00:16:58,953 --> 00:17:00,192
- Seriously. - Let's do this.

454
00:17:00,193 --> 00:17:02,293
Let's do our best to repay them.

455
00:17:02,793 --> 00:17:04,293
Please try your best, Ji Sung.

456
00:17:05,563 --> 00:17:06,833
Please.

457
00:17:07,563 --> 00:17:09,003
I'll do my best to stay in shape.

458
00:17:09,603 --> 00:17:10,863
Please do your best.

459
00:17:11,103 --> 00:17:12,832
- Let's do this. - Let's do a group cheer.

460
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:13,973
- Let's do this. - Okay.

461
00:17:14,103 --> 00:17:16,272
All right. One, two, three.

462
00:17:16,273 --> 00:17:19,273
- We love you, Wannables! - We love you, Wannables!

463
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:25,883
(As always, Wannables will be part of their day.)

464
00:17:26,753 --> 00:17:31,753
(Wanna One wraps up their first trip to the Wanna Base.)

465
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:46,432
(They return to the Wanna Base on a sunny spring day.)

466
00:17:46,433 --> 00:17:47,572
Wanna be the one!

467
00:17:47,573 --> 00:17:50,343
(Who's the first member to arrive?)

468
00:17:50,543 --> 00:17:52,443
Wanna Base.

469
00:17:54,013 --> 00:17:55,212
Wanna Base.

470
00:17:55,213 --> 00:17:57,733
(Seong Wu arrives at the Wanna Base with a spring in his step.)

471
00:17:57,983 --> 00:17:58,983
How do I open the door?

472
00:17:59,383 --> 00:18:02,953
(Showing off his silly side as soon as he arrives)

473
00:18:03,183 --> 00:18:04,653
(Is anyone in here?)

474
00:18:04,723 --> 00:18:05,723
Oh, this is how I open it.

475
00:18:05,724 --> 00:18:07,044
(He successfully opens the door.)

476
00:18:07,963 --> 00:18:09,723
All right.

477
00:18:10,423 --> 00:18:11,433
Wait.

478
00:18:11,863 --> 00:18:14,063
(Don't forget that you have to jump in.)

479
00:18:16,003 --> 00:18:18,573
(Still struggling to check into the base the second time around)

480
00:18:18,873 --> 00:18:21,033
(The first thing he does after checking in...)

481
00:18:21,603 --> 00:18:22,773
Have you been well, Kuan Lin?

482
00:18:23,603 --> 00:18:27,143
My gosh. You didn't even go home. You've been here the whole time.

483
00:18:27,913 --> 00:18:29,313
I bet you were cold.

484
00:18:30,343 --> 00:18:32,453
Have you been standing here the whole time?

485
00:18:34,683 --> 00:18:36,553
You're working hard here.

486
00:18:37,023 --> 00:18:39,293
(Have another great day!)

487
00:18:39,953 --> 00:18:41,763
Should I go with a cool jump today?

488
00:18:43,223 --> 00:18:44,223
(A cool jump?)

489
00:18:44,224 --> 00:18:45,333
(Striding)

490
00:18:45,533 --> 00:18:46,633
Jump.

491
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:48,703
I'm going to make it look cool today.

492
00:18:49,203 --> 00:18:51,132
I was too cautious the last time I jumped in.

493
00:18:51,133 --> 00:18:52,133
(Stepping down timidly)

494
00:18:52,533 --> 00:18:54,643
You should do a forward roll while jumping in.

495
00:18:56,203 --> 00:18:57,603
I don't think I can do it.

496
00:18:58,973 --> 00:19:00,343
(He gives up right away.)

497
00:19:00,543 --> 00:19:01,643
I'll just jump.

498
00:19:02,113 --> 00:19:03,113
(Screaming)

499
00:19:03,543 --> 00:19:06,053
(He screams first and then jumps in.)

500
00:19:06,553 --> 00:19:08,123
We're back here.

501
00:19:08,353 --> 00:19:09,582
Look.

502
00:19:09,583 --> 00:19:10,623
(Cheering)

503
00:19:11,523 --> 00:19:12,653
My gosh!

504
00:19:13,623 --> 00:19:15,263
- What is this? - Look.

505
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:17,022
Gosh, it smells so good.

506
00:19:17,023 --> 00:19:19,262
- Walnut cakes. My gosh. - And tornado potatoes.

507
00:19:19,263 --> 00:19:20,663
- We also have churros. - Gosh.

508
00:19:21,033 --> 00:19:22,102
This combo is popular at rest stops.

509
00:19:22,103 --> 00:19:24,333
Right. The rest stop snacks. Look how good they look.

510
00:19:24,733 --> 00:19:26,032
(I love it!)

511
00:19:26,033 --> 00:19:27,033
How can we not eat them?

512
00:19:27,034 --> 00:19:29,042
(It's impossible to hold back on these delicious treats.)

513
00:19:29,043 --> 00:19:30,543
(Screaming)

514
00:19:30,743 --> 00:19:33,113
Wait. I hear them screaming inside.

515
00:19:33,713 --> 00:19:34,713
What's going on?

516
00:19:35,113 --> 00:19:36,113
Something's up.

517
00:19:36,583 --> 00:19:38,383
You know? Something's up.

518
00:19:38,613 --> 00:19:39,613
Good morning.

519
00:19:39,783 --> 00:19:40,783
Guys!

520
00:19:40,784 --> 00:19:43,153
Hurry up!

521
00:19:43,283 --> 00:19:44,653
(Amazed)

522
00:19:44,823 --> 00:19:45,892
That's new.

523
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,422
(The Activity Zone has changed too?)

524
00:19:47,423 --> 00:19:48,423
(Rushing over)

525
00:19:48,424 --> 00:19:49,762
Woo Jin, we have more game machines now.

526
00:19:49,763 --> 00:19:50,893
(Upgraded Activity Zone)

527
00:19:51,363 --> 00:19:52,563
We got the hammer instead.

528
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:54,093
There's a boxing machine?

529
00:19:54,563 --> 00:19:55,932
We should have a bet with this.

530
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:57,439
(The newly improved Activity Zone will provoke their competitiveness.)

531
00:19:57,463 --> 00:19:58,733
(What else has changed?)

532
00:19:59,403 --> 00:20:01,472
Hey, how come he's already sleeping here?

533
00:20:01,473 --> 00:20:03,302
(Kang Daniel)

534
00:20:03,303 --> 00:20:04,543
Daniel came early.

535
00:20:05,013 --> 00:20:06,013
(There's Daniel who's taking a nap.)

536
00:20:06,014 --> 00:20:07,472
(And are these clothes?)

537
00:20:07,473 --> 00:20:09,112
We have new outfits.

538
00:20:09,113 --> 00:20:11,083
- It's a tracksuit for our show. - That's cute.

539
00:20:11,983 --> 00:20:13,753
Guys!

540
00:20:15,483 --> 00:20:17,653
Let's change into our outfit and then meet up.

541
00:20:18,153 --> 00:20:19,493
(Are they listening?)

542
00:20:19,653 --> 00:20:20,692
Here's an announcement.

543
00:20:20,693 --> 00:20:22,799
We'll change into our outfit and then have breakfast.

544
00:20:22,823 --> 00:20:23,823
What?

545
00:20:23,963 --> 00:20:26,733
Guys, let's change into our outfit and then meet up.

546
00:20:27,063 --> 00:20:30,462
I'll take it that you all heard the announcement.

547
00:20:30,463 --> 00:20:31,833
(That's it for the announcement.)

548
00:20:32,403 --> 00:20:33,873
Let's eat, guys.

549
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:36,303
You know what this reminds me of?

550
00:20:36,473 --> 00:20:37,542
A rest stop.

551
00:20:37,543 --> 00:20:39,042
- Give me the fishcake on a stick. - Oh, this?

552
00:20:39,043 --> 00:20:41,012
- Try this. - Oh, fishcake on a stick.

553
00:20:41,013 --> 00:20:42,013
My gosh.

554
00:20:42,013 --> 00:20:43,013
(Taking a bite)

555
00:20:43,243 --> 00:20:45,412
I want the tornado potatoes. Wait, there's tteokbokki too.

556
00:20:45,413 --> 00:20:46,853
- This is no joke. - I put it there.

557
00:20:46,913 --> 00:20:48,529
This is great. It feels like a rest stop here.

558
00:20:48,553 --> 00:20:49,553
Isn't this so good?

559
00:20:49,923 --> 00:20:50,923
It's so good.

560
00:20:51,793 --> 00:20:52,793
It's really tasty.

561
00:20:52,794 --> 00:20:55,822
Guys, everyone gets this dish at rest stops. Roasted potatoes.

562
00:20:55,823 --> 00:20:57,522
- Roasted potatoes. - Roasted potatoes.

563
00:20:57,523 --> 00:20:58,633
Sir, can I have some?

564
00:21:00,393 --> 00:21:01,732
Is he the owner of the rest stop?

565
00:21:01,733 --> 00:21:03,732
- I'm not the owner. - I mean...

566
00:21:03,733 --> 00:21:04,802
Really?

567
00:21:04,803 --> 00:21:06,102
- You're not the owner? - Sir.

568
00:21:06,103 --> 00:21:07,783
- Wait. Sir. - That over there is my shop.

569
00:21:08,033 --> 00:21:09,772
Over there. It's Ong Seong Wu's Barge.

570
00:21:09,773 --> 00:21:11,402
He makes squeezed juice.

571
00:21:11,403 --> 00:21:13,613
(There lives Mr. Ong who sells squeezed juice.)

572
00:21:13,843 --> 00:21:17,083
(Mr. Ong insists on freshly squeezed juice made from real fruit.)

573
00:21:17,483 --> 00:21:18,912
Do you want me to make squeezed juice...

574
00:21:18,913 --> 00:21:20,382
- for breakfast? - Really?

575
00:21:20,383 --> 00:21:22,753
- My gosh. Then... - I don't want it.

576
00:21:23,223 --> 00:21:25,022
- Then I don't want it. - My gosh.

577
00:21:25,023 --> 00:21:26,192
- What is it? - I'm fine too.

578
00:21:26,193 --> 00:21:27,822
- What is it? - Squeezed juice for breakfast.

579
00:21:27,823 --> 00:21:28,943
- This... - I don't want it.

580
00:21:29,823 --> 00:21:31,092
It's pretty good.

581
00:21:31,093 --> 00:21:32,809
(The story of Mr. Ong who may have to close the shop in 30 minutes)

582
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:34,263
I should go and change too.

583
00:21:34,663 --> 00:21:36,332
(It's peaceful at the Food Zone again.)

584
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:37,603
Come on!

585
00:21:38,603 --> 00:21:39,832
(They accidentally bump their butts.)

586
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:41,003
Your bottom...

587
00:21:41,273 --> 00:21:43,543
How much farther will you stick it out?

588
00:21:43,743 --> 00:21:45,742
- Come on. Let me eat. - Seriously.

589
00:21:45,743 --> 00:21:47,043
How much farther...

590
00:21:47,213 --> 00:21:48,512
You're in my way.

591
00:21:48,513 --> 00:21:51,212
Fifty cents.

592
00:21:51,213 --> 00:21:52,213
I don't want it.

593
00:21:52,214 --> 00:21:53,313
(You don't want it?)

594
00:21:54,253 --> 00:21:57,822
You know what? I wasn't going to offer this to you.

595
00:21:57,823 --> 00:21:59,992
- Seriously. - Come on.

596
00:21:59,993 --> 00:22:01,323
- Hold on. - No.

597
00:22:01,453 --> 00:22:02,792
(The slushy seller's secret weapon is...)

598
00:22:02,793 --> 00:22:04,433
(the lethal red-capped bottle of liquor.)

599
00:22:04,493 --> 00:22:05,833
(Coughing)

600
00:22:06,093 --> 00:22:08,933
(Kuan Lin gave us the strongest liquor ever.)

601
00:22:09,203 --> 00:22:11,263
(The present from Kuan Lin burned their throats.)

602
00:22:11,573 --> 00:22:12,903
(The memories are flooding back.)

603
00:22:13,473 --> 00:22:14,772
- Can you mix my drink with that? - It's still here.

604
00:22:14,773 --> 00:22:17,473
- What? - Director Jang is keeping it here.

605
00:22:17,643 --> 00:22:19,642
- Really? He asked us to keep it? - He's keeping it here?

606
00:22:19,643 --> 00:22:21,172
- He wants us to keep it here. - My gosh.

607
00:22:21,173 --> 00:22:22,419
- This is good. - We need his permission.

608
00:22:22,443 --> 00:22:24,712
He shouldn't have done that.

609
00:22:24,713 --> 00:22:26,413
(Director Jang is really something else.)

610
00:22:26,753 --> 00:22:27,753
- Jae Hwan. - Yes.

611
00:22:27,754 --> 00:22:29,122
- We have more corn dogs left. - There's so much food for you.

612
00:22:29,123 --> 00:22:30,283
Yes!

613
00:22:30,623 --> 00:22:32,753
There's no holding back now. I must eat some of this.

614
00:22:33,453 --> 00:22:35,762
- There's so much food for you. - I'm eating way too much.

615
00:22:35,763 --> 00:22:37,393
I'm eating a lot. This is bad.

616
00:22:37,763 --> 00:22:38,963
(Crunch)

617
00:22:39,163 --> 00:22:40,862
- The food was so good. - Seriously.

618
00:22:40,863 --> 00:22:42,902
- We rarely eat breakfast. You know? - Exactly.

619
00:22:42,903 --> 00:22:44,973
And this is an unusual combo for breakfast too.

620
00:22:45,303 --> 00:22:47,332
- Who eats this for breakfast? - Right.

621
00:22:47,333 --> 00:22:49,873
Who eats tornado potatoes and churros for breakfast?

622
00:22:50,443 --> 00:22:51,472
(Who do you think?)

623
00:22:51,473 --> 00:22:52,672
(It's you, Wanna One.)

624
00:22:52,673 --> 00:22:54,313
(I'm stuffed.)

625
00:22:55,043 --> 00:22:56,542
- Wait, Jin Young isn't here? - What?

626
00:22:56,543 --> 00:22:58,042
(Say something.)

627
00:22:58,043 --> 00:22:59,782
- Jin Young isn't here. - He's running late.

628
00:22:59,783 --> 00:23:00,783
He's running late.

629
00:23:00,784 --> 00:23:03,144
(Jin Young is here. He's not late. He's just an introvert.)

630
00:23:04,183 --> 00:23:05,753
What?

631
00:23:06,453 --> 00:23:07,722
(Why is Ji Sung surprised?)

632
00:23:07,723 --> 00:23:10,722
- What is it? - We only have that much time today.

633
00:23:10,723 --> 00:23:13,403
- We don't have much time today. - Right. It's a one-day gathering.

634
00:23:13,493 --> 00:23:15,132
- We're not sleeping over today. - We...

635
00:23:15,133 --> 00:23:17,003
Daniel's guesthouse is closed today.

636
00:23:17,563 --> 00:23:18,803
How many hours do we have left?

637
00:23:18,933 --> 00:23:20,202
- Fifteen hours. - Fifteen hours and thirty minutes.

638
00:23:20,203 --> 00:23:22,123
- That's not enough time. - You're eating again?

639
00:23:22,173 --> 00:23:24,273
(After the chaotic breakfast, )

640
00:23:25,173 --> 00:23:28,712
(they walk around to find something to do.)

641
00:23:28,713 --> 00:23:29,713
Let's take a nap.

642
00:23:30,583 --> 00:23:31,583
(Ringing)

643
00:23:33,813 --> 00:23:35,923
(Startled)

644
00:23:36,223 --> 00:23:37,223
What?

645
00:23:37,283 --> 00:23:38,523
Is Shin Seung Ho here again?

646
00:23:38,723 --> 00:23:39,763
(Hooked on the Wanna Base)

647
00:23:39,923 --> 00:23:40,923
(It's Seung Ho again?)

648
00:23:41,623 --> 00:23:43,423
But we just got here.

649
00:23:43,723 --> 00:23:44,723
Is it delivery food?

650
00:23:44,724 --> 00:23:46,509
We didn't order any food. How can it be delivery food?

651
00:23:46,533 --> 00:23:47,693
Let me go out and check.

652
00:23:50,003 --> 00:23:51,163
Let me go out and check.

653
00:23:51,873 --> 00:23:54,603
(What? Dae Hwi will go out and check?)

654
00:23:55,243 --> 00:23:57,019
(You should run if it's a job for the youngest.)

655
00:23:57,043 --> 00:23:58,043
Me?

656
00:23:58,103 --> 00:24:01,812
(Dae Hwi just kept on laughing, instead of reading the room.)

657
00:24:01,813 --> 00:24:02,842
(The baby of the group is going to sleep.)

658
00:24:02,843 --> 00:24:04,403
(The baby of the group is going to go.)

659
00:24:05,353 --> 00:24:06,413
Who is it?

660
00:24:07,553 --> 00:24:09,552
(Our dear Dae Hwi...)

661
00:24:09,553 --> 00:24:12,793
(has improved.)

662
00:24:13,153 --> 00:24:14,793
(Dae Hwi quickly goes to the door.)

663
00:24:15,423 --> 00:24:17,563
- Is someone here? - I don't know. Let me check.

664
00:24:18,693 --> 00:24:19,693
What?

665
00:24:20,533 --> 00:24:22,763
What? We have a package!

666
00:24:22,863 --> 00:24:24,363
We have a package?

667
00:24:24,603 --> 00:24:25,703
We got a package.

668
00:24:26,373 --> 00:24:27,493
Is it for product placement?

669
00:24:28,233 --> 00:24:29,903
We got a package.

670
00:24:30,273 --> 00:24:31,542
Who ordered this package?

671
00:24:31,543 --> 00:24:33,242
- Why is it so big? - What did we order?

672
00:24:33,243 --> 00:24:35,082
- Where is it from? - Who ordered this?

673
00:24:35,083 --> 00:24:36,312
Where is it from?

674
00:24:36,313 --> 00:24:39,353
"Wanna Base, Beautiful-gu, Energetic City."

675
00:24:39,913 --> 00:24:41,112
Hey, this is from Gocheok Sky Dome.

676
00:24:41,113 --> 00:24:42,182
- Right. - Really?

677
00:24:42,183 --> 00:24:43,682
- Seong Wu. - Do they want us to perform again?

678
00:24:43,683 --> 00:24:44,752
- You startled me. - There are two.

679
00:24:44,753 --> 00:24:46,222
(Powerfully unboxing the package)

680
00:24:46,223 --> 00:24:48,253
- There are two boxes. - What is this?

681
00:24:48,793 --> 00:24:50,663
- Another one? - Wait. This is...

682
00:24:51,093 --> 00:24:52,792
- There's another one inside. - Is this...

683
00:24:52,793 --> 00:24:54,893
- Is this a matryoshka? - It's a matryoshka.

684
00:24:55,063 --> 00:24:56,702
No, there's another box inside.

685
00:24:56,703 --> 00:24:58,163
- What? - Come on.

686
00:24:58,873 --> 00:24:59,873
Hey.

687
00:24:59,874 --> 00:25:01,232
(Woo Jin the Kindergartener is angry at the boxes.)

688
00:25:01,233 --> 00:25:03,072
- No. - Hey.

689
00:25:03,073 --> 00:25:04,272
There's another one inside.

690
00:25:04,273 --> 00:25:05,972
- There's another one. - Let's not open it.

691
00:25:05,973 --> 00:25:07,072
Let's not open it.

692
00:25:07,073 --> 00:25:08,912
- Let's send it back. - Let's return it.

693
00:25:08,913 --> 00:25:10,612
- They're teasing us. - Sure.

694
00:25:10,613 --> 00:25:12,252
- Let's send it back. - We should send it back.

695
00:25:12,253 --> 00:25:13,682
- Send it back. - Yes.

696
00:25:13,683 --> 00:25:15,022
I don't know whom it's from.

697
00:25:15,023 --> 00:25:16,329
But why would anyone send this to us?

698
00:25:16,353 --> 00:25:17,799
(They calm down and open the box again.)

699
00:25:17,823 --> 00:25:18,892
As long as we're together,

700
00:25:18,893 --> 00:25:20,092
- we can get through anything. - Hey, look at this.

701
00:25:20,093 --> 00:25:21,392
- Five boxes. - Yes.

702
00:25:21,393 --> 00:25:22,463
We're getting close.

703
00:25:22,593 --> 00:25:23,723
(At last...)

704
00:25:23,923 --> 00:25:25,062
We're getting close to another box.

705
00:25:25,063 --> 00:25:26,143
We already have five boxes.

706
00:25:28,903 --> 00:25:29,903
(Unleashing his anger)

707
00:25:30,503 --> 00:25:31,602
(Even the second-oldest member is acting out.)

708
00:25:31,603 --> 00:25:33,903
- By the way, judging by the weight, - Hey.

709
00:25:34,373 --> 00:25:35,373
There's nothing inside.

710
00:25:35,873 --> 00:25:37,742
- What on earth is this? - I bet it's a letter.

711
00:25:37,743 --> 00:25:39,242
(They're on their 6th box.)

712
00:25:39,243 --> 00:25:40,372
- What is it? - This is driving me crazy.

713
00:25:40,373 --> 00:25:41,573
(They're on their 7th box.)

714
00:25:42,583 --> 00:25:43,583
Come on.

715
00:25:43,584 --> 00:25:44,913
(They're on their 8th box.)

716
00:25:45,583 --> 00:25:47,952
- This has to be the last one. - Is this it?

717
00:25:47,953 --> 00:25:49,929
(They're on their 9th box. This isn't the same clip.)

718
00:25:49,953 --> 00:25:51,022
This has to be the last box.

719
00:25:51,023 --> 00:25:52,422
- There's nothing inside. - It must be.

720
00:25:52,423 --> 00:25:53,969
(No, it's not. They're on their 10th box.)

721
00:25:53,993 --> 00:25:56,123
(Father, please stop giving us boxes.)

722
00:25:56,293 --> 00:25:58,592
This has to be the last box for real.

723
00:25:58,593 --> 00:25:59,963
- One, two, three. - Two, three.

724
00:26:00,233 --> 00:26:05,533
(Screaming)

725
00:26:06,703 --> 00:26:07,833
Are you kidding me?

726
00:26:07,933 --> 00:26:08,972
- Hey. - My gosh.

727
00:26:08,973 --> 00:26:11,073
- This is so annoying. Isn't it? - Hey, hold on.

728
00:26:12,113 --> 00:26:14,313
- Come on. It's so annoying. - Right.

729
00:26:15,113 --> 00:26:17,612
Oh, is it a cassette?

730
00:26:17,613 --> 00:26:19,113
- Oh, right! - I see.

731
00:26:19,153 --> 00:26:20,352
- That must be it. - Right?

732
00:26:20,353 --> 00:26:21,512
- Yes. - It might be a cassette.

733
00:26:21,513 --> 00:26:23,123
- A cassette. - That's it.

734
00:26:23,253 --> 00:26:24,683
(A while ago during their arrival)

735
00:26:25,053 --> 00:26:26,722
(When they were looking around the Wanna Base, )

736
00:26:26,723 --> 00:26:28,329
(they spotted a cassette player which wasn't there before.)

737
00:26:28,353 --> 00:26:29,362
(A Bluetooth speaker on Day One)

738
00:26:29,363 --> 00:26:30,363
(A cassette player today)

739
00:26:30,593 --> 00:26:32,633
(A cassette player replaced the Bluetooth speaker.)

740
00:26:33,763 --> 00:26:36,663
(It's symbolic to our group.)

741
00:26:38,503 --> 00:26:41,002
(A cassette is a symbolic object...)

742
00:26:41,003 --> 00:26:44,743
(that serves as a bridge to Wanna One's universe.)

743
00:26:47,073 --> 00:26:49,882
(It represented an eternal connection...)

744
00:26:49,883 --> 00:26:52,653
(with Wannables through infinity-shaped cassettes.)

745
00:26:52,913 --> 00:26:54,513
- I think it's a cassette. - One...

746
00:26:54,653 --> 00:26:56,122
Actually, nothing can be smaller...

747
00:26:56,123 --> 00:26:57,622
- than this box. - Right.

748
00:26:57,623 --> 00:26:59,192
- Right. It has to be the last one. - Seriously.

749
00:26:59,193 --> 00:27:00,522
- This has to be it. - Yes.

750
00:27:00,523 --> 00:27:02,363
- Hey, it really was a cassette. - No way.

751
00:27:02,863 --> 00:27:04,022
(A cassette is really in the box.)

752
00:27:04,023 --> 00:27:05,262
Ji Hoon was right.

753
00:27:05,263 --> 00:27:07,103
- How did you figure it out? - Hey, it says...

754
00:27:07,163 --> 00:27:08,432
- Hey, it says, "To Wannable." - This is...

755
00:27:08,433 --> 00:27:10,032
- "To Wannable." - What's going on?

756
00:27:10,033 --> 00:27:11,979
We have to find a player and put it in. Over there.

757
00:27:12,003 --> 00:27:13,872
They replaced the Bluetooth speaker.

758
00:27:13,873 --> 00:27:15,473
Right. I noticed the change.

759
00:27:15,743 --> 00:27:18,303
All right. Let's listen to it together.

760
00:27:19,173 --> 00:27:20,743
Is it a voice message?

761
00:27:21,213 --> 00:27:23,213
It said, "To Wannable." So it has to come from us.

762
00:27:23,513 --> 00:27:26,652
(Putting behind all kinds of speculations, )

763
00:27:26,653 --> 00:27:28,553
(they play the cassette.)

764
00:27:30,023 --> 00:27:31,752
(I promise you)

765
00:27:31,753 --> 00:27:33,553
(That I won't forget you)

766
00:27:35,163 --> 00:27:36,222
- Wait. - What?

767
00:27:36,223 --> 00:27:37,563
Wait, it's our song.

768
00:27:38,123 --> 00:27:39,232
What?

769
00:27:39,233 --> 00:27:41,209
("I PROMISE YOU" resonates throughout the Wanna Base.)

770
00:27:41,233 --> 00:27:42,733
- What's going on? - This is random.

771
00:27:43,333 --> 00:27:44,432
This is random.

772
00:27:44,433 --> 00:27:45,502
(I promise you)

773
00:27:45,503 --> 00:27:48,103
(I'll love you more and treat you better)

774
00:27:48,433 --> 00:27:49,903
(Creaking)

775
00:27:50,603 --> 00:27:52,513
- Hey! - Wait, the door is open!

776
00:27:54,913 --> 00:27:56,643
- Hey! - Wait, the door is open!

777
00:27:56,913 --> 00:27:58,313
- What's going on? - What is this?

778
00:27:58,913 --> 00:28:01,052
- What's going on? - Oh, my. What's this?

779
00:28:01,053 --> 00:28:03,123
- My goodness. - Hey, the headphones!

780
00:28:03,283 --> 00:28:04,453
- What's going on? - My gosh.

781
00:28:04,623 --> 00:28:05,753
- What? - What?

782
00:28:06,023 --> 00:28:08,423
(What's all this?)

783
00:28:08,763 --> 00:28:10,692
- Where is this place? - What's going on?

784
00:28:10,693 --> 00:28:11,862
- Where are we? - What is it?

785
00:28:11,863 --> 00:28:14,263
- I see a lot of stuff on the table. - What's going on?

786
00:28:14,633 --> 00:28:16,963
(Lyric sheets fill the table.)

787
00:28:17,433 --> 00:28:19,202
(They see a tablet PC containing mystery tracks...)

788
00:28:19,203 --> 00:28:20,673
(and headsets.)

789
00:28:21,173 --> 00:28:23,372
(Staring)

790
00:28:23,373 --> 00:28:25,872
(Scanning the table)

791
00:28:25,873 --> 00:28:28,113
I see. Is this for our fan song?

792
00:28:28,883 --> 00:28:31,582
(Before their first shoot, they discussed releasing an album.)

793
00:28:31,583 --> 00:28:33,913
(But we decided to work as Wanna One again.)

794
00:28:34,383 --> 00:28:35,582
(We should definitely release a song for Wannables.)

795
00:28:35,583 --> 00:28:38,993
(I want to give back a lot more to our fans.)

796
00:28:39,593 --> 00:28:43,522
(With a strong desire to give back for their unwavering patience, )

797
00:28:43,523 --> 00:28:47,393
(Wanna One decided to make a fan song as their first step.)

798
00:28:47,893 --> 00:28:49,402
"A blind test for the fan song."

799
00:28:49,403 --> 00:28:51,732
"You'll release a fan song for Wannables."

800
00:28:51,733 --> 00:28:53,672
"Listen to all ten songs..."

801
00:28:53,673 --> 00:28:56,543
"and choose one."

802
00:28:56,603 --> 00:28:58,842
I guess we get to pick the fan song.

803
00:28:58,843 --> 00:29:00,842
(I love it.)

804
00:29:00,843 --> 00:29:02,342
- This is great. This will be fun. - We can listen to them...

805
00:29:02,343 --> 00:29:03,812
with the headphone?

806
00:29:03,813 --> 00:29:05,682
- Yes. They must be connected. - How is that possible?

807
00:29:05,683 --> 00:29:07,882
- Let's pick our fan song. - Okay.

808
00:29:07,883 --> 00:29:09,822
- So we'll decide on our song today. - Okay?

809
00:29:09,823 --> 00:29:14,523
(The members of Wanna One also participated in the process.)

810
00:29:14,593 --> 00:29:16,522
- So we're going to decide here? - This is a song camp.

811
00:29:16,523 --> 00:29:18,492
Let's bring some food here.

812
00:29:18,493 --> 00:29:19,893
(His appetite is on another level.)

813
00:29:21,093 --> 00:29:22,302
- Yes. - We can eat while we listen.

814
00:29:22,303 --> 00:29:24,132
- Hey, should I bring some snacks? - It will put us in a good mood.

815
00:29:24,133 --> 00:29:25,232
Let's have some refreshments.

816
00:29:25,233 --> 00:29:26,702
- Let's bring some refreshments. - Exactly.

817
00:29:26,703 --> 00:29:28,472
- Let's go and bring a slushy. - I'll get us some refreshments.

818
00:29:28,473 --> 00:29:30,402
- Let's bring refreshments. - Yes.

819
00:29:30,403 --> 00:29:31,902
We have to listen to ten songs.

820
00:29:31,903 --> 00:29:34,472
- Right. We have a lot of time. - We need at least 30 minutes.

821
00:29:34,473 --> 00:29:35,542
Let's get refreshments.

822
00:29:35,543 --> 00:29:37,242
- Had we known... - Over there.

823
00:29:37,243 --> 00:29:39,782
- We didn't have to hurry. - Right.

824
00:29:39,783 --> 00:29:41,882
- We'll need one of these. - We need food.

825
00:29:41,883 --> 00:29:43,583
- Let's grab sweet potato sticks. - Okay.

826
00:29:43,853 --> 00:29:45,352
- I'll get butter bagel chips too. - Okay.

827
00:29:45,353 --> 00:29:47,293
- Pretzels are tasty too. - Yes. That too.

828
00:29:47,323 --> 00:29:48,692
- Let's grab jelly too. - Grab a bag of jelly.

829
00:29:48,693 --> 00:29:50,092
Grab the truffle-flavored chips.

830
00:29:50,093 --> 00:29:51,823
- Slushy. - Make sure to bring the slushy.

831
00:29:52,033 --> 00:29:53,732
- This is sugar-free. - Yes.

832
00:29:53,733 --> 00:29:54,792
Let's enjoy this session.

833
00:29:54,793 --> 00:29:56,233
- And we... Right. - Exactly.

834
00:29:56,803 --> 00:29:59,632
I hope there's a song we decide on unanimously.

835
00:29:59,633 --> 00:30:02,602
- If we do, that would be amazing. - If it's a unanimous decision...

836
00:30:02,603 --> 00:30:04,002
But that would be almost impossible.

837
00:30:04,003 --> 00:30:05,842
- Right. Everyone likes... - There are ten songs.

838
00:30:05,843 --> 00:30:07,042
Different styles of music.

839
00:30:07,043 --> 00:30:08,682
- I'm sure they're all good songs. - Right.

840
00:30:08,683 --> 00:30:10,082
- I think many songwriters... - I'm so grateful.

841
00:30:10,083 --> 00:30:12,652
Sent us great songs when they heard we'd release a song...

842
00:30:12,653 --> 00:30:14,853
- after many years. - Exactly.

843
00:30:15,383 --> 00:30:18,652
I'll pick a song that makes me cry.

844
00:30:18,653 --> 00:30:19,722
Fan songs...

845
00:30:19,723 --> 00:30:22,022
- should be touching, right? - That's right.

846
00:30:22,023 --> 00:30:24,292
I agree. It should capture our story well.

847
00:30:24,293 --> 00:30:25,692
(Spotting something)

848
00:30:25,693 --> 00:30:28,062
Ji Hoon, can I play the song now?

849
00:30:28,063 --> 00:30:30,162
Are you good? You're so focused on your food.

850
00:30:30,163 --> 00:30:31,803
- I see. Okay. - Should I just play it?

851
00:30:32,933 --> 00:30:35,102
(A slushy eater has entered the listening room.)

852
00:30:35,103 --> 00:30:38,043
(It's been confirmed that the slushy eater is Park Ji Hoon.)

853
00:30:38,643 --> 00:30:41,243
(The Winking Cutie loves slushy.)

854
00:30:42,043 --> 00:30:43,563
(He licks off a stray drop of slushy.)

855
00:30:43,713 --> 00:30:45,752
- You can play it. - Let's go.

856
00:30:45,753 --> 00:30:47,452
We should relax like Ji Hoon when we listen to songs.

857
00:30:47,453 --> 00:30:48,652
- Right. - Yes.

858
00:30:48,653 --> 00:30:50,652
- I'll play the first one. - Okay.

859
00:30:50,653 --> 00:30:52,252
Gosh, I'm looking forward...

860
00:30:52,253 --> 00:30:53,893
- to the song. - I'm excited.

861
00:30:54,453 --> 00:30:57,523
(The first song of the blind listening party, "GIFTED")

862
00:31:00,633 --> 00:31:03,703
(They stop laughing and focus on the song.)

863
00:31:05,163 --> 00:31:08,273
(Focused with his favorite slushy)

864
00:31:38,903 --> 00:31:40,632
(The first song, "GIFTED," ends.)

865
00:31:40,633 --> 00:31:42,072
This is a great song.

866
00:31:42,073 --> 00:31:43,272
It's a good song.

867
00:31:43,273 --> 00:31:44,872
How should I say it?

868
00:31:44,873 --> 00:31:47,042
The lyrics, "gifted," really stick with you.

869
00:31:47,043 --> 00:31:48,072
- It stands out. - Yes.

870
00:31:48,073 --> 00:31:49,942
It's repetitive, so it stands out.

871
00:31:49,943 --> 00:31:52,453
But what does it mean, Dae Hwi?

872
00:31:55,583 --> 00:31:57,852
When I heard the lyrics, I knew it right away.

873
00:31:57,853 --> 00:32:01,422
I thought, "This guy deeply understands the emotions..."

874
00:32:01,423 --> 00:32:03,263
"Wanna One is going through."

875
00:32:03,323 --> 00:32:05,092
I thought this was the perfect line for Dae Hwi.

876
00:32:05,093 --> 00:32:07,263
And it would suit his vocal register too.

877
00:32:08,363 --> 00:32:11,102
If you think about it, meeting each other, forming a group,

878
00:32:11,103 --> 00:32:13,332
and meeting Wannables feel like a gift.

879
00:32:13,333 --> 00:32:16,242
So all of these moments make us feel gifted...

880
00:32:16,243 --> 00:32:17,603
with such blessings.

881
00:32:18,843 --> 00:32:21,272
Don't you think that's what the song means?

882
00:32:21,273 --> 00:32:22,982
- That's what you think, right? - I think that's the meaning.

883
00:32:22,983 --> 00:32:24,312
- That's the message, right? - Yes.

884
00:32:24,313 --> 00:32:25,812
- By the way, - Yes.

885
00:32:25,813 --> 00:32:28,922
I've been waiting for the rap part of this song.

886
00:32:28,923 --> 00:32:31,622
I know everything there is to know about how he writes rap.

887
00:32:31,623 --> 00:32:32,823
(Come on, man.)

888
00:32:32,953 --> 00:32:34,452
Is that what you expected?

889
00:32:34,453 --> 00:32:36,393
It's just as I expected.

890
00:32:36,993 --> 00:32:39,433
(Laughing)

891
00:32:40,093 --> 00:32:41,562
(You're listening to the rap that screams Dae Hwi...)

892
00:32:41,563 --> 00:32:43,002
(according to his 9-year colleague, Woo Jin.)

893
00:32:43,003 --> 00:32:45,263
(Easily recognizing Dae Hwi's style)

894
00:32:45,803 --> 00:32:47,602
- The rap flow... - Is it that obvious?

895
00:32:47,603 --> 00:32:49,402
Screams Dae Hwi.

896
00:32:49,403 --> 00:32:50,502
- Dae Hwi wrote it? - I'm certain he wrote it.

897
00:32:50,503 --> 00:32:52,172
It's supposed to be a blind session.

898
00:32:52,173 --> 00:32:53,742
I'll be honest. I knew it was his the moment I listened...

899
00:32:53,743 --> 00:32:56,083
- to the intro. - Really?

900
00:32:58,883 --> 00:33:01,583
(Wise Hwang knew it as soon as he heard the song.)

901
00:33:01,783 --> 00:33:03,752
- It's the chord progression... - How did he know?

902
00:33:03,753 --> 00:33:05,522
- Right. It's the chord progression. - he likes to use.

903
00:33:05,523 --> 00:33:08,052
I guess we know each other fairly well.

904
00:33:08,053 --> 00:33:09,992
- Exactly. - I got a feeling.

905
00:33:09,993 --> 00:33:11,762
What did you think, Jin Young?

906
00:33:11,763 --> 00:33:13,762
- I liked the song, but... - Okay.

907
00:33:13,763 --> 00:33:15,092
- But? - What?

908
00:33:15,093 --> 00:33:16,233
(But?)

909
00:33:16,703 --> 00:33:18,432
- What? - But?

910
00:33:18,433 --> 00:33:19,903
Will he turn into Lee Seung Chul?

911
00:33:20,373 --> 00:33:24,743
(All eyes are fixed on his lips.)

912
00:33:25,473 --> 00:33:27,472
I really liked the song. But...

913
00:33:27,473 --> 00:33:30,013
the chorus sounded a bit familiar.

914
00:33:30,383 --> 00:33:31,383
(Dae Hwi's melodic development sounded familiar to him.)

915
00:33:31,383 --> 00:33:32,383
Right.

916
00:33:33,313 --> 00:33:35,883
That's my feedback. But it was really good, Dae Hwi.

917
00:33:36,123 --> 00:33:37,222
The melody sounded familiar?

918
00:33:37,223 --> 00:33:38,352
- But it was really good, Dae Hwi. - Okay.

919
00:33:38,353 --> 00:33:40,522
- A familiar chord progression. - A familiar chord progression.

920
00:33:40,523 --> 00:33:43,023
- But the lyrics were so beautiful. - I agree.

921
00:33:43,763 --> 00:33:44,962
I'll play the second song.

922
00:33:44,963 --> 00:33:45,963
- Okay. - Okay.

923
00:33:47,493 --> 00:33:49,362
(The second song of the blind listening party)

924
00:33:49,363 --> 00:33:50,603
("Again, Spring Breeze")

925
00:33:51,003 --> 00:33:53,643
(Dae Hwi listens to the second song as a member and a songwriter.)

926
00:33:53,773 --> 00:33:56,103
(Bae Bae is focused too.)

927
00:33:56,673 --> 00:33:59,773
(Compared to "GIFTED," the intro has an upbeat, rhythmic vibe.)

928
00:34:00,443 --> 00:34:02,913
(Will it be another song from a member of Wanna One?)

929
00:34:04,143 --> 00:34:06,183
(Reading the room)

930
00:34:12,423 --> 00:34:15,353
(He can't put down his favorite slushy.)

931
00:34:16,763 --> 00:34:18,993
(Hold on.)

932
00:34:27,673 --> 00:34:31,073
(This vocal style sounds familiar.)

933
00:34:33,373 --> 00:34:36,383
(A prime suspect according to the members)

934
00:34:38,083 --> 00:34:39,552
(The 2nd candidate, "Again, Spring Breeze")

935
00:34:39,553 --> 00:34:42,683
(He's focused on the song, clueless that his secret is out.)

936
00:34:44,153 --> 00:34:46,092
(It's Sung Woon's song, right?)

937
00:34:46,093 --> 00:34:47,593
(I think it is.)

938
00:34:58,103 --> 00:34:59,573
As for the second song,

939
00:34:59,603 --> 00:35:01,133
what stood out to me the most was...

940
00:35:01,633 --> 00:35:03,772
it didn't have any English lyrics.

941
00:35:03,773 --> 00:35:05,402
- I see. - Right.

942
00:35:05,403 --> 00:35:06,812
- As if that was his intention. - Yes.

943
00:35:06,813 --> 00:35:07,813
I think it was his intention.

944
00:35:07,814 --> 00:35:11,213
When you write lyrics, it's hard not to include English lyrics.

945
00:35:11,543 --> 00:35:14,953
Because it didn't have any English lyrics, I was impressed.

946
00:35:15,253 --> 00:35:17,682
He wrote the lyrics as if he was writing a letter.

947
00:35:17,683 --> 00:35:19,992
- Right. That was the vibe. - The lyrics were coherent.

948
00:35:19,993 --> 00:35:23,762
If we were to write a letter to our fans, it'd sound like this...

949
00:35:23,763 --> 00:35:24,763
- content-wise. - Right.

950
00:35:24,764 --> 00:35:26,932
- Our main concept was cassettes. - Right.

951
00:35:26,933 --> 00:35:28,532
Before the chorus, I heard...

952
00:35:28,533 --> 00:35:29,732
- the sound of a cassette playing. - Right.

953
00:35:29,733 --> 00:35:30,832
- It was great. - That's the key point.

954
00:35:30,833 --> 00:35:31,863
I liked that.

955
00:35:32,003 --> 00:35:34,473
(Toward the end of Verse 1 in "Again, Spring Breeze")

956
00:35:34,533 --> 00:35:37,473
(The sound of a cassette playing kicks in here.)

957
00:35:38,243 --> 00:35:40,642
- It was great. I liked that. - That's the key point.

958
00:35:40,643 --> 00:35:42,272
- What do you think, Sung Woon? - I liked that.

959
00:35:42,273 --> 00:35:44,013
- You just can't stop smiling. - No.

960
00:35:44,913 --> 00:35:45,913
I...

961
00:35:45,914 --> 00:35:47,813
(Yes?)

962
00:35:47,913 --> 00:35:49,483
I like the song because...

963
00:35:50,253 --> 00:35:53,153
(Why is he so shy?)

964
00:35:53,393 --> 00:35:55,092
It sounds like this guy can't speak English.

965
00:35:55,093 --> 00:35:56,613
(Criticizing himself because he's shy)

966
00:35:57,523 --> 00:35:59,032
(Seeing a shy Sung Woon is a first.)

967
00:35:59,033 --> 00:36:00,993
That might not have been his intention.

968
00:36:01,233 --> 00:36:03,103
(What on earth is he saying?)

969
00:36:04,663 --> 00:36:06,772
I realized rather late that it might've been Sung Woon's song.

970
00:36:06,773 --> 00:36:08,833
Right. I didn't realize it at first.

971
00:36:09,503 --> 00:36:10,842
(I see. This was Sung Woong's song.)

972
00:36:10,843 --> 00:36:12,203
(Suddenly nodding his head)

973
00:36:12,543 --> 00:36:14,312
I'm getting the vibe that this songwriter...

974
00:36:14,313 --> 00:36:16,542
might be rough around the edges in person.

975
00:36:16,543 --> 00:36:17,782
But how could he write...

976
00:36:17,783 --> 00:36:18,982
- such a delicate song? - He's elegant when he writes music.

977
00:36:18,983 --> 00:36:20,012
Right. He must turn into someone else.

978
00:36:20,013 --> 00:36:21,982
I get what you mean. This is how the lyrics sound to me.

979
00:36:21,983 --> 00:36:23,323
"We trusted."

980
00:36:23,783 --> 00:36:25,182
I can sense the way he talks from the lyrics.

981
00:36:25,183 --> 00:36:26,352
(The lyrics remind him of a certain someone's voice.)

982
00:36:26,353 --> 00:36:27,922
"We trusted."

983
00:36:27,923 --> 00:36:28,923
(The beginning is important.)

984
00:36:28,923 --> 00:36:29,923
(I saved him.)

985
00:36:29,923 --> 00:36:30,923
(Slow down.)

986
00:36:30,923 --> 00:36:31,923
(So you'll show us?)

987
00:36:32,063 --> 00:36:33,762
(An unexpected observation makes him dizzy.)

988
00:36:33,763 --> 00:36:35,932
- "We trusted." - "Hey."

989
00:36:35,933 --> 00:36:37,162
- "We trusted." - "We trusted."

990
00:36:37,163 --> 00:36:38,463
(Copycats are everywhere.)

991
00:36:38,703 --> 00:36:41,573
(It went down the wrong pipe.)

992
00:36:41,673 --> 00:36:44,072
- He might be that type. You know? - Yes. I can picture his tone.

993
00:36:44,073 --> 00:36:46,712
I can clearly notice the way he talks from his lyrics.

994
00:36:46,713 --> 00:36:48,312
- "It's only a momentary goodbye." - Right.

995
00:36:48,313 --> 00:36:50,213
"It's only a momentary goodbye."

996
00:36:51,213 --> 00:36:53,453
- Number 3? - Let's listen to the 3rd song.

997
00:36:54,413 --> 00:36:56,352
(The third song of the blind listening party)

998
00:36:56,353 --> 00:36:57,523
("Again, One")

999
00:37:03,063 --> 00:37:05,763
(Ji Sung spots a guy with an anxious gaze.)

1000
00:37:15,773 --> 00:37:18,343
(He's completely focused on the song.)

1001
00:37:33,723 --> 00:37:36,093
(We found the songwriter.)

1002
00:37:36,363 --> 00:37:38,693
(Twitching)

1003
00:37:49,673 --> 00:37:51,103
(Are you serious?)

1004
00:37:53,513 --> 00:37:57,443
(Jae Hwan is unable to hide his singing style.)

1005
00:38:05,623 --> 00:38:07,452
(Whatever. I give up.)

1006
00:38:07,453 --> 00:38:08,993
(The 3rd candidate, "Again, One")

1007
00:38:21,003 --> 00:38:22,772
(Surprised)

1008
00:38:22,773 --> 00:38:24,403
(Impressed)

1009
00:38:24,903 --> 00:38:26,812
- Oh, the cassette player. - Jae Hwan, it's a great song.

1010
00:38:26,813 --> 00:38:27,972
Jae Hwan, I like it.

1011
00:38:27,973 --> 00:38:29,383
Did Jae Hwan write this?

1012
00:38:29,813 --> 00:38:31,412
I really liked the pre-chorus.

1013
00:38:31,413 --> 00:38:33,282
- There was a transition. - Right.

1014
00:38:33,283 --> 00:38:35,883
- The melody built up nicely. - Right.

1015
00:38:36,323 --> 00:38:38,853
(The intensifying melody of the pre-chorus stood out.)

1016
00:38:39,623 --> 00:38:41,623
(Instantly getting into it)

1017
00:38:42,293 --> 00:38:43,762
(Great job, Jjaeni.)

1018
00:38:43,763 --> 00:38:45,723
It's a great song.

1019
00:38:46,063 --> 00:38:48,362
In my opinion, this kind of band-style music...

1020
00:38:48,363 --> 00:38:50,362
is incredibly trendy...

1021
00:38:50,363 --> 00:38:53,132
- in the music industry these days. - Right.

1022
00:38:53,133 --> 00:38:56,442
As a group, we haven't tried band-style music like this.

1023
00:38:56,443 --> 00:38:59,442
I'm also curious to see how a rock ballad song...

1024
00:38:59,443 --> 00:39:02,782
would come out if we were to sing it.

1025
00:39:02,783 --> 00:39:04,412
